content:
NPTEL NEW

<https://nptel.ac.in/>
¬≠

*Meet the ‚ÄúNPTEL Sir‚Äù*

With over 60 NPTEL courses completed, Dr. Amitbodh Upadhyay exemplifies
lifelong learning. From guiding students in sustainability and innovation
to motivating faculty across disciplines, his story is a testament to
NPTEL‚Äôs impact on personal growth, leadership, and academic excellence.

scientific research into real-world startups with insights on funding,
business models, and execution.

Ideal for innovators & researchers!

Applications are now open for SURC 2025, taking place on Dec 7‚Äì8 at Azim
Premji University, Bengaluru! Undergraduate students across India engaged
in research in biology, chemistry, physics, mathematics, or computer
science can apply to present talks or posters .

*Apply before 18th July*

*3D India Symposium 2025: Advancing Additive Manufacturing **üß©*

Join industry leaders and innovators at the *3D India Symposium 2025*,
happening on *2nd July* at *IIT Madras, Chennai*. With case studies, expert
sessions, and a dedicated exhibition, the event will showcase real-world
applications of additive manufacturing across aerospace, defence, medical,
automotive, and more.

subject: Film Your Hackathon Journey and Be Part of the AI Gold Rush Story üìΩÔ∏è
snippet: Greg Isenberg and an Emmy Award-winning crew are filming a documentary to explore the AI Gold Rush and they'll be featuring builders from the World's Largest Hackathon. The series will reach
content:
Greg Isenberg and an Emmy Award-winning crew are filming a documentary to explore the AI Gold Rush and they'll be featuring builders from the World's Largest Hackathon. The series will reach millions, making it an incredible opportunity to share your story, showcase your project, and maybe even land your first customer.

Happy Friday builders!

We‚Äôve partnered with our friends at Entri (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/MVsGVTRvSMjW46pS-B3T_nshW8cYYgJ5xMCCgN72QTZR3lcq-W69sMD-6lZ3n1W8rvkPv4Jm4FlW88Wz8g25T2n5W1Cqc9y1SP2mkN5xXM959XC_0W6fs3JT1PgdT0W13rxzq3srqLzN7P074zpng5HW3tM3sj2QVzg9N7Gww6cYK5dVVyydZ_4TVbHsN5tmqqkVjftJW8WQTyJ5Hm_bcW3wtvTl8j2yDWW5gB74b2Jm6wdN7bKG5bxtcllW5XnMr_2qdGc-W72zz5V44bS5ZW4P5wcC8BBSYJW5dJzWK6X12k4W3t6Jhs86RwRCf8RRnLq04 ) to bring you this email full of exciting news and updates.

First, we can‚Äôt stress enough how inspiring it‚Äôs been to see you all hackin‚Äô away this week, whether it‚Äôs solo, as part of a team, or just collabing and co-working in the same spaces on Discord together (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/MVsGVTRvSMjW46pS-B3T_nshW8cYYgJ5xMCCgN72QTZR3lcq-W69sMD-6lZ3m8VmZwS58lFYLzW2P1G7n80zNW8VpMVYB6dR2L_N66Wppt7WMDtW3Z7PDR2CqYQ8W6hFHHz2JS588W8vdVTc8cVv0sVzWCX34nwt0fW2lgTMn5nPL-vW6m7VGZ12nRG8N3CMYnqxTsq_MkmgM7yQjPbW1prXKW8QYd_kW70dTxT61zG-YW7S8BwK2T1GS9W9l-PHS1ShLs8W20fDHq71-lChW3cJgMp7nQC1yW7sDTkQ3BBQXcW5n1dSR8HKSHff2R7Q-n04 ) . You should feel proud of what you‚Äôve already accomplished, and we‚Äôre cheering big for you as you approach the halfway mark.

Team rules clarification

A lot of you had questions about submitting entries as a team, so we‚Äôve made it more clear in the official rules (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/MVsGVTRvSMjW46pS-B3T_nshW8cYYgJ5xMCCgN72QT-q3lcq-W7lCdLW6lZ3l1W2sYDHJ2sgGWdW7v2tyT562jKJW3MPGqY5KyXD_W4hYZW92SWFLJW8QrRfM3wYQqxW4g7Fx-7_stVqW7_cVJm2GsmzrW5nd1-q2K45X2W83mXdY5RbFKFW79TxYR10lM4lVBRx321SgS9qW1wXrHQ92nNhTW8wqnrm7Z760HW4hcJQn1tgJB5W3_DGPL7q8ZNsW5VjmP37ZHMDGW9gJBtw3kZR87W3CKvtz7hQzhbV2T9zs7ZFktsW2w-jfg2zwhNvN5g9QH03N19jVTr0B289TpwvW2XFXY71ZkTHmW7PnkTz3Z_kWYdz9Sqj04 ) . TL;DR: A team or org must appoint and authorize one individual to represent, act, and enter a submission on their behalf, and all team members must meet the official eligibility requirements.

Builder Pack update

If you registered but haven‚Äôt received your Builder Pack yet, we‚Äôre on it. With nearly 100k builders, we ran out of Bolt codes faster than expected. We‚Äôre generating more and reaching out to sponsors for extra codes. As soon as we‚Äôve got everything, the rest of the packs will ship via email. We appreciate your patience!

Get featured in the Hackathon Docuseries

Greg Isenberg and an Emmy Award-winning crew are filming a documentary (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/MVsGVTRvSMjW46pS-B3T_nshW8cYYgJ5xMCCgN72QT-q3lcq-W7lCdLW6lZ3l6W4jdz9s1jJbPQW6px5sb87R9qbW7b630-35dNJSW5KKvN07Q_3x5W5xMWfY1cG1ncW6X03br90t6Z4W1MY5mg1WJmT7N6LXtt6_sc9sW2ZVn_Q7R_r4NW1hpBCn4pKtNDN1D0P1mPKhdnN1Y3kLGMTfF9W83CZMY2B__y9W7hB3GH885bKNW2BS2qf2xntFNW67qKKZ6WmsCBW1f562L8wlyBtW6srlKV7Sg0BKW7TKLwr4rHXDYW27D08f33Qpc7W5l8vcJ64VH-gN7sRQ-tnFvsXV-pJKX1mxdxfW1VGvh846zzxnf5fJyS604 ) to explore the AI Gold Rush and they'll be featuring builders from the World's Largest Hackathon. The series will reach millions, making it an incredible opportunity to share your story, showcase your project, and maybe even land your first customer.

If you‚Äôre interested in being considered in the documentary:

- Film yourself (and your team) working on your project, telling your story, and sharing your progress. Content can include selfie or vlog-style videos, Zoom and Discord calls, and anything else you capture throughout your journey.
- Fill out the submission form (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/MVsGVTRvSMjW46pS-B3T_nshW8cYYgJ5xMCCgN72QT-K3lcq-W7Y8-PT6lZ3pXVsc8794Z6W40VvPHXd2dk0fHW6Y-NZS26YJlsVTnQ968fl46-VJnncV6cKqgjW78fg6t2Z_6DDW7TBnK22GFg37W3y2_KQ2WlXzsW5dSn_D6ST5P9W8V0NLp55_hRRW6XL-TL1Yp_V9W7pkzly2hPzzzW90P2Kh5ccX7FW2f_mX08cF5g0W87HCYl5DpvZTW15G1_C3Mn23nW3cFPHH261lxLW2nt5K72mJ7yhW4-pDlm6prLwgVfNk683bj7NfW6zGDNw8xM4n9W62sTdq5c3b8ZW6nknQT8KWKMJW7G6gWh1tZcPbW4HvbN97yvgmJN9f4YzHkf-CLf3YFtZb04 ) , where you will also upload your footage.

Get featured
(https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/MVsGVTRvSMjW46pS-B3T_nshW8cYYgJ5xMCCgN72QT-K3lcq-W7Y8-PT6lZ3pXVsc8794Z6W40VvPHXd2dk0fHW6Y-NZS26YJlsVTnQ968fl46-VJnncV6cKqgjW78fg6t2Z_6DDW7TBnK22GFg37W3y2_KQ2WlXzsW5dSn_D6ST5P9W8V0NLp55_hRRW6XL-TL1Yp_V9W7pkzly2hPzzzW90P2Kh5ccX7FW2f_mX08cF5g0W87HCYl5DpvZTW15G1_C3Mn23nW3cFPHH261lxLW2nt5K72mJ7yhW4-pDlm6prLwgVfNk683bj7NfW6zGDNw8xM4n9W62sTdq5c3b8ZW6nknQT8KWKMJW7G6gWh1tZcPbW4HvbN97yvgmJN9f4YzHkf-CLf3YFtZb04 )

Entri Challenger Prize

As a proud sponsor of the Bolt Hackathon, Entri builds solutions that simplify domains for everyday users. Hackathon participants can win $25,000 in the Custom Domain Challenge (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/MVsGVTRvSMjW46pS-B3T_nshW8cYYgJ5xMCCgN72QT_03lcq-W8wLKSR6lZ3njW4wwLHq3037l8W4KKtQN4dWkdGW2LjqrQ6RshQnW2BWkHX7R8ScRW6YlNFl1HG8s5W5bMC3h4qNjBBW2wl4hc6tzh7BW3sl9pL2dqf-wW74nryd7g-1qRW2rznpS90Hs00W1qdZWl7MQbdPW3Hcvx77_ThtfW4dD3d71SzFssVyFkDg62Nls0W8FG11f4NGWfkW5n0HH2181vkqW1q8jld3jW8g4N947d_gpZLrYW3rplkR2VQ2G0VNlYxT7d1m5kW84CqTT3DWMzkW7pk2Zj7W0JlsW53KKHw62mh9lW8j2SVn45Gk0KW9kf2Dp1zxKzcW46VzZh4DMRgsVwCF-T4NBHLGW7J3Mmm4MwhH-dcT5-n04 ) . Whether it's clever, bold or brilliantly simple, simply register your domain name via Entri or IONOS; the most creative domain name wins!

subject: Invitation to participate in 11th International Yoga Day - Online Debate Competition organized by¬†IIIM¬†NSS¬†Cell
snippet: Dear Students, Greetings from IIIM NSS Cell!!! To celebrate the 11th International Yoga Day, Indukaka Ipcowala Institute of Management (IIIM) - NSS Cell has organized an Online Debate competition on
content:
Dear Students,

Greetings from IIIM NSS Cell!!!

To celebrate the *11th International Yoga Day,* Indukaka Ipcowala Institute
of Management (IIIM) - NSS Cell has organized an *Online Debate competition*
 on *June 20, 2025 (Friday).*



*Online Debate Competition ‚Äì Event Details:*

*Date:* June 20, 2025
*Time:* 10:30 AM Onward
*Theme:* Yoga for One Earth, One Health* (Topics to be provided one hour
prior to the scheduled start of the competition)*

*Registration Process:*
Interested participants are requested to register latest by *June 19,
2025* *till
12 PM* using the following link: https://forms.gle/Qzf1YCSnSnDxqFX68

*Online Debate Format:*
*The structure and flow of the debate will be determined based on the total
number of registered participants. Topics will be shared with participants
one hour prior to the competition.*

*Proposed Rounds:*

   1. *Preliminary Round:*
      - Each participant will speak for 3 minutes, either *for* or
*against* the
      motion.
      - Top-performing speakers from the preliminary round will advance to
      the final round.
   2. *Final Round (Crossfire & Closing Statement):*
      - A crossfire round will be conducted, where the selected
      participants will engage in a Q&A session with each other and the judges.
      - Each finalist will then present a 1-minute closing statement.

*Judging Criteria:*

   - Content & Knowledge
   - Delivery & Clarity
   - Rebuttal & Defence
   - Engagement & Time Adherence

*Certificates:*


   - Winners will be awarded 1st, 2nd, and 3rd prizes.
   - All participants will receive a Certificate of Participation.


Together let's make this International Yoga Day memorable. We look forward
to your cooperation at this extraordinary
International Yoga Day Celebration.



Please contact* IIIM NSS Coordinators: *Dr. Poonam Amrutia (+91 94295
58484); Mr. Brijesh Patel (+91 97370 23027) for further details.


*Kruten Patel*
*Executive Officer (Corporate Communications)*

We‚Äôve partnered with Anthropic to bring Claude Sonnet 4 to all Bolt users! Push your build to the next level.

Hey there,

We wanted to give you some Monday updates as we head into week 2 of the World‚Äôs Largest Hackathon! First, based on questions from participants, we‚Äôve clarified some rules that will help you submit with more confidence. Watch the quick n‚Äô easy video update here (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VVLRd38JmXmkW5CZSQ77SRKP5W3Bmyl95xChHPN2XT74v3lcq-W7lCdLW6lZ3lyW2BXy0y5nLL1sW1crJgw3wr57NW8TYt2D45GF3pW3BN0KN6qY79cW7DZD_t97qVSMN6MHjHnmgwdbN2Z_S2wmVMXbW8JxZ4K6YKlbBW5FhJkl6WpYLqW881SRV2tm1j5W8ScvN12dC_XZW46Kxl_1DQndQW1c8qHy2208fbW1VbLt34DHgSQN344lbWMNnlmW2GkXZf3Q063bVLj0wv3XjPSpVz1GVt4NsZbHW4xr8Nt4F8bMVW15DS_43mwHbpW3ZdQdk5TfQn0W84MLFc5ZZ-mBW7Z7CtH8KyvhnW9k4CN48TrGXNf2f_2kv04 ) , or review the official rules (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VVLRd38JmXmkW5CZSQ77SRKP5W3Bmyl95xChHPN2XT74v3lcq-W7lCdLW6lZ3lRW1FBxny3k_hT0W7_XVDT9cwCK0W3gNWpn8P0B4zW8tRXRs99Y1wXW1YHWbH3bybx3W32hMLt1BSsdxVmY1KY4QNbSnW1YDzwZ1m7nZ5W6TjnRG2sPNszW3W3-D98zhsw6W5vT5b75ndH5LW7P02Vs94FS8VW2vMBd16zxwRMW2_rrd22qsRmsN3Sp_Fn__fD_MxfXJ87sTVfVygvWP7CgzTzT9vJm73F8_3N5typCRYCmhYW8fwv9q1xlsRGW9fzdsp5mr6zBN1tnC8qr6mKHW7c23nn1gPH7QW9brFxP4rg_xXf4Nrlwg04 ) for the full rundown.

It is not too late to register for the hackathon! Register (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VVLRd38JmXmkW5CZSQ77SRKP5W3Bmyl95xChHPN2XT73W3lcq-W69sMD-6lZ3n-W3q8zc43ZjQnzW1pR_Jx8zp7CsW1HzJCJ5FfgrTW27g2Mk2RtlbFW1m3N0k3lTX_SW7LF7BM4ryk8PW1TsK1Z9dsqf9VdC3d-4H8dBKN8FQLYHfK0MDW1nF2gy26DzbMN1g3lt6RchqXW1rfHvM43gMsYW4JY1136jmpXhW3fRyCn3Dyz55W4pDGD64cnf8NW4PvvN019p0SkW5HJmwc5Yn4q_W3QF4bg2dXT_xW2qxkGm3rrbRQW77-b374h0H37f2jpXmF04 ) for the hackathon to get your FREE Builder Pack which includes FREE Bolt Pro and much more. Existing Bolt subscribers may use the code for $30 off any subscription upgrades.The pack is sent to you via email within 48 hours of signing up, so be sure to sign-up asap!

We‚Äôve partnered with Anthropic to bring Claude Sonnet 4 to all Bolt users

The wait is over! Claude Sonnet 4 is now live on Bolt üëå One of the smartest models out there, fully integrated into your favorite AI builder. Push your build to the next level. Bolt-Anthropic-1x1-V3-1 (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VVLRd38JmXmkW5CZSQ77SRKP5W3Bmyl95xChHPN2XT74v3lcq-W7lCdLW6lZ3pgN4RsbJZGN3jcW6BfvXj6N-rKPW3CpGFC1w_l2QW4v_l6q3LC1MXW1B_XGB6kBdpCW3n8s8J74yBbvW2tzW_f3lptZ3VHh_w784-DQxW8ftqB-81HpvnW4Lq_fj2Kp9jHW7zWClj7fZjCbW7FD1p48b1bPDW74-L9s1ywF13W1N2S0Z3MzXBhW1dZXz85gTgVpW7Jfz-F5tQWtQVgL6Vs5zd4nCW8qHM0q8zNQScW8klTxS7V5KV0N78_ldxK1TQVW1lRKDY4G_7DKN3mJ_whkT7CRW4100xS6Nwzm4W2l0qM73Bc7XWf10V0n004 )

Still need your Builder Pack?

If you have not received your builder pack, here‚Äôs what to do:

- Step 1: Make sure you have registered on hackathon.dev  (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VVLRd38JmXmkW5CZSQ77SRKP5W3Bmyl95xChHPN2XT73W3lcq-W69sMD-6lZ3n-W3q8zc43ZjQnzW1pR_Jx8zp7CsW1HzJCJ5FfgrTW27g2Mk2RtlbFW1m3N0k3lTX_SW7LF7BM4ryk8PW1TsK1Z9dsqf9VdC3d-4H8dBKN8FQLYHfK0MDW1nF2gy26DzbMN1g3lt6RchqXW1rfHvM43gMsYW4JY1136jmpXhW3fRyCn3Dyz55W4pDGD64cnf8NW4PvvN019p0SkW5HJmwc5Yn4q_W3QF4bg2dXT_xW2qxkGm3rrbRQW77-b374h0H37f2jpXmF04 )

snippet: GitHub Education Student Newsletter May 2025 May brought fresh AI tools, career wisdom, and community wins‚Äîeverything below is ready for you to watch, fork, or RSVP. What's inside: üèóÔ∏è Build 2025
content:
***********************************
GitHub Education Student Newsletter
***********************************

--------
May¬†2025
--------

May brought fresh AI tools, career wisdom, and community wins‚Äîeverything below is ready for you to watch, fork, or RSVP.

*What's inside:*

* üèóÔ∏è Build 2025 highlights
* üéØ Vibe coding roadmap
* üå± Junior-dev success guide
* üéì 500 Campus Experts
* üõ† Maintainer Month rewind
* üì∫ Open Source Friday spotlight
* üë©‚Äçüíª Hack¬†Club Athena Award
* ‚õ∫ MLH Hackcon 2025
* üåç Copilot Global Bootcamp
* ‚≠êÔ∏è Trending repo: developer-roadmap

üèóÔ∏è Build 2025: five launches you can try today
----------------------------------------------

Build dropped a bundle of student-friendly AI updates‚Äîhere's what you can spin up right now:

*1) GitHub Copilot Chat goes open-source.* The extension's code is being merged into the main microsoft/vscode repo, so you can fork it, add custom slash-commands, and submit pull requests guided by the CONTRIBUTING doc.

*2) GitHub Copilot agent mode in VS Code Insiders.* Install the latest Insiders build and the Copilot Chat extension; agent mode now appears automatically in the Chat view, chaining refactors, test runs, and rollbacks‚Äîan ideal playground for prompt engineering.

*3) GitHub Copilot coding agent (public preview).* Click Run with Copilot on any issue and the agent branches, edits, commits, and opens a pull request with a full audit log. The preview is currently limited to Copilot Pro + and Enterprise subscribers for now.

*4) GitHub Models Hub.* Pin GPT-4o, Claude 3, or Gemini 1.5 to a repo, benchmark latency versus quality, and share prompt presets‚Äîno API-key juggling required.

*5) Microsoft Copilot multi-agent DevOps preview.* Watch three Microsoft Copilot agents collaborate: an infra agent provisions Azure Bicep, a doc agent rewrites the README, and a work-item agent files follow-up issues‚Äîyour crash course in AI-driven teamwork.

Browse the full Book of News ( https://news.microsoft.com/build-2025-book-of-news/ )

üéØ "Vibe coding" roadmap: your GPS to AI mastery
-----------------------------------------------

The new guide splits the AI journey into four snack-size phases: a Python and math refresh, data-wrangling drills with Kaggle, hands-on LLM engineering, and a ship-it capstone that deploys a model to the new GitHub Models Hub. Each phase links to starter repos, good-first-issue boards, and 90-second explainer videos so you can build a portfolio as you learn.

Finish by crafting a README with a model card, evaluation notebook, and GIF demo‚Äîexactly what hiring managers (and Copilot) parse first. Bonus: the guide teaches you to A/B test GPT-4o vs Claude 3 using Copilot's Model Picker.

Follow the roadmap ( https://github.blog/ai-and-ml/vibe-coding-your-roadmap-to-becoming-an-ai-developer/ )

üå± Thriving as a junior engineer: field-tested playbook
------------------------------------------------------

First internship or grad scheme on the horizon? The latest GitHub Blog article distills advice from engineering managers at Shopify, NASA, and Stripe. Core habits: ask "why" in every code review, keep a living "aha!" journal, and time-box rabbit holes so you ship and learn in parallel.

Author Yelyzaveta Kramarenko suggests pairing sessions, writing docs as you debug, and contributing to open source to beat impostor syndrome. Leads get guidance too: shape bite-size tickets, use scaffolded PR templates, and celebrate small-win merges.

The downloadable checklist doubles as a 1-on-1 agenda‚Äîperfect for your next stand-up.

Read the full guide ( https://github.blog/developer-skills/career-growth/how-to-thrive-as-a-junior-engineer-tips-and-insights/ )

üéì About 500 GitHub Campus Experts‚Äîand how to join them
------------------------------------------------------

The program that began with 15 pioneers in 2017 has now reached *500 Campus Experts across 67 countries*. In 2024 alone they ran 1,240 workshops, mentored 28K peers, and secured $320K in sponsorship for student hackathons.

Campus Experts receive detailed support for events they run on their campuses and in their communities, and a bunch of other amazing perks for active members. We're looking forward to the next 500 Experts, and one of them can be you!

Applications reopen in July, so start drafting your campus-impact proposal now!

Become a Campus Expert ( https://github.com/education/students/campus-expert )

üõ† Maintainer Month rewind: students, mentors, momentum
------------------------------------------------------

*Kick-off: MLH Fellowship showcase.* One hundred twenty-eight fellows merged 620 pull requests into 18 open-source projects‚Äîincluding a GPU compiler, a Django security dashboard, and new ESLint rules for Astro. Veteran maintainers like Mehdi Khodja streamed weekly code reviews so students could watch "why" as well as "what." Learn more about the MLH Fellowship ( https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/159852 ).

*Mid-month: Appwrite AMA + showcase.* The backend-as-a-service team fielded 70+ community questions on auth pitfalls, edge scaling, and their new AI-assist CLI. Meanwhile, the Built with Appwrite ( https://builtwith.appwrite.io/ ) gallery crossed 120 student apps‚Äîeverything from a pizza tracker to a mindfulness bot.

*Finale: New Relic √ó OpenTelemetry live demo.* Maintainer Reese Lee instrumented the Astro Shop demo and turned a single PR into latency graphs and error heat-maps‚Äîall live on Twitch. Missed it? The VOD is waiting on our GitHub Education Twitch channel ( https://www.twitch.tv/videos/2470777872 ).

Relive Maintainer Month ( https://maintainermonth.github.com )

üì∫ Open Source Friday: feature your project live on stream
---------------------------------------------------------

Every Friday at 1 PM ET, hosts Andrea Griffiths and Kedasha Kerr chat with a maintainer on GitHub's main Twitch channel ( https://www.twitch.tv/github ). Projects like Homebrew and Astro doubled contributor traffic within 48 hours, and each episode lives forever on the YouTube playlist ( https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PL0lo9MOBetEFmtstItnKlhJJVmMghxc0P&feature=shared ).

*Why join?* Showcase your work to thousands of devs, demo new features live, and inspire first-time contributors. *How to apply:* make sure your repo meets the project criteria ( https://github.com/githubevents/open-source-friday/blob/main/admin/project-criteria.md ) (OSI license + CONTRIBUTING guide + 5 help-wanted issues), then open the guest-invite template ( https://github.com/githubevents/open-source-friday/issues/new?template=osf-guest-invite.yml&assignees=AndreaGriffiths11%2CLadyKerr&labels=open-source%2Copen-source-friday%2Cpending%2Ctwitch ).

You'll get a rehearsal call, custom Twitch overlays, and promotion to GitHub's multi-million-dev social channels. Game engines, bio-data sets, niche CLI tools‚Äîall are welcome.

Apply for a slot ( https://github.com/githubevents/open-source-friday )

Watch previous episodes ‚ñ∂Ô∏é ( https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PL0lo9MOBetEFmtstItnKlhJJVmMghxc0P&feature=shared )

üë©‚Äçüíª Hack Club Athena: earn an award, join NYC hackathon
-------------------------------------------------------

Girls and non-binary teens: ship *three public projects by Oct 31* to claim the inaugural Athena Award and secure a seat at the 36-hour hackathon in NYC's Civic Hall (Nov 15-16). Expect $100 k in prizes, mentorship from NASA, Stripe, and GitHub engineers, and a travel stipend for the first 100 qualifiers worldwide.

Weekly Discord office hours pair beginners with seasoned mentors, and every participant earns cloud credits plus an Athena hoodie once their first PR lands.

RSVP for Athena ( https://athena.hackclub.com/ )

‚õ∫ MLH Hackcon 2025: camp for hackathon organizers
-------------------------------------------------

*Aug 22-24 ‚Ä¢ Camp Pontiac, NY.* Hackcon pulls 300+ organizers into two immersive days of sponsor-hunting tips, DEI workshops, and risk-management war stories‚Äîcapped with lake swims, night hikes, and the legendary tie-dye bar.

Day 1 is a single-track summit; Day 2 is an unconference so you can troubleshoot your own event challenges. Early-bird tickets vanish Jun 30; scholarship apps shut Jul 15.

Grab your ticket ( https://ti.to/mlh/mlh-hackcon-2025 )

üåç Level-up with the Copilot Global Bootcamp
-------------------------------------------

Ready to super-charge your coding with AI? The *GitHub Copilot Global Bootcamp* is back‚Äîbringing free online tracks and 30+ in-person workshops to cities from S√£o Paulo to Fukuoka. You‚Äôll dive into Copilot Chat, prompt engineering, and real-world team workflows inside Visual Studio Code.

*Join live online in your language:*

* üáßüá∑ Portuguese ‚Äî June¬†24 & 26 @ 7 PM (UTC-3 Bras√≠lia)
* üá∫üá∏ English ‚Äî July 8 & 10 @ 9 AM PT ¬∑ 12 PM ET
* üá™üá∏ Spanish ‚Äî July 8 & 10 @ 11 AM PT ¬∑ 2 PM ET ¬∑ 8 PM CET

Prefer face-to-face learning? Microsoft MVPs are hosting hands-on labs worldwide between *June 17 ‚Äì 28*. Check the map on the registration page for a workshop near you.

Complete the Bootcamp and you‚Äôll unlock a shot at the new Microsoft Applied Skills credential: ‚ÄúAccelerate app development with GitHub Copilot.‚Äù It‚Äôs the perfect r√©sum√© booster‚Äîvalidates your AI-powered development chops and costs nothing.

Save my seat ‚Äî free ( https://lnkd.in/gThesY4v )

‚≠êÔ∏è Trending repo: developer-roadmap (324 k‚≠ê)
--------------------------------------------

With clickable maps for everything from frontend to DevOps, developer-roadmap just crossed 324 k stars after launching an interactive "AI Engineer" track and a toggle for budget-friendly resources. Each node expands to mini-guides, project ideas, and interview questions crowdsourced from big-tech hiring managers.

Fork it to draft your personalized plan, subscribe to the monthly refresh newsletter, or tackle one of 230 open "first-timer" issues to give back while you level up.

Explore the repo ( https://github.com/kamranahmedse/developer-roadmap )

üëã Until next time
-----------------

Thanks for celebrating Maintainer Month with us. Keep coding, keep collaborating, and we'll see you in June with fresh resources for your summer projects.

- The GitHub Education Team

Follow us

subject: Nomenclature Competition I Multi Utility Building @ CHARUSAT
snippet: Dear Students, CHARUSAT is excited to invite your creative suggestions for naming our Multi-Utility Complex. The facility is a versatile space for CSIC, CIVF, HRDC, COE, IT Cell, IQAC, conference rooms
content:
Dear Students,

CHARUSAT is excited to invite your creative suggestions for *naming our
Multi-Utility Complex.*
The facility is a versatile space for CSIC, CIVF, HRDC, COE, IT Cell, IQAC,
conference rooms, paperless exam halls, an exam control room, and
multitudes of related services. It is designed to cater to the diverse
needs of CHARUSAT's unique initiatives and will play a pivotal role in
enhancing the overall campus experience.


*Criteria for Nomenclature:*

   - Should reflect Vedic/Sanskrit terminology‚Äîeasily memorable
   - Should be meaningful and relevant to the facility
   - Should have Clarity, brevity, and creativity
   - Should have a touch of academia or knowledge


üéÅPrize: The best fit name will be awarded a cash prize of ‚Çπ11,000/- by the
prime donor of this facility, Shri Devang Patel (Nadiad).


Click to fill out the form <https://forms.gle/WDvwYgL4uC2DBHMi9>
*Deadline*: Submit your response before May 30, 2025.


*Kruten Patel*
*Executive Officer (Corporate Communications)*

subject: Final Call : Free Internship in Embedded Systems : Written Test Schedule & Guidelines
snippet: Dear Anand Chaniyara, Greetings from Emertxe. The login credentials for taking up the Internship screening test has been sent to your email id. In case you did not receive it, you can reset the
content:
Dear *Anand Chaniyara,*

Greetings from *Emertxe.*

The login credentials for taking up the Internship screening test has 
been sent to your email id. In case you did not receive it, you can 
reset the password. The written test *is extended till 6th May 2025 11 
P.M.* Please *ensure you take up the test any time before the deadline*.

*
Steps to reset the password:*


1. Go to URL - *https://moodle.emertxe-group.com/login/forgot_password.php*
2. *Enter your email address in Email address field (Username)*
3. Click on Search. This is send an email to reset the password
4. *Open your email and check for the password reset email from Emertxe*
Note: Please check in Inbox/Updates/Spam as well. Otherwise search for 
Emertxe LMS
5. Follow the instructions in the email. Please note a strong password 
is expected.

After resetting the password, you can login again with the new password.
Click on Micro Controller Internship Screening - B13 to take the test.
You can also directly take the test using this link, after login: 
*https://moodle.emertxe-group.com/mod/quiz/view.php?id=103519* 
<https://moodle.emertxe-group.com/mod/quiz/view.php?id=103519>

Note: Ignore if you have already taken the test.

-- 

Regards,
Sneha N | Manager - University Relations & Internships,
Emertxe Information Technologies,
#83 Farah Towers, 1st Floor,
MG Road,
Bangalore - 560001

Dear Students,

Looking to add an exciting and valuable skill to your profile?

The *Faculty of Humanities (FoH), CHARUSAT* is offering a *30-hour offline
interactive training program* titled *‚ÄúFrench For All‚Äù*, from *12th May to
30th May, 2025‚Äî* specially designed for *beginners and language enthusiasts*
.

In today‚Äôs global job market, just having technical or academic skills is
no longer enough. *Learning a foreign language like French can give you a
competitive edge*, opening up new career opportunities, international
exposure, and cultural insights.

This is your chance to:

‚úîÔ∏è ‚Å£Explore the beauty and power of the French language

(LSRW)
‚úîÔ∏è Learn in a fun, engaging classroom environment

 *The detailed brochure is attached for your reference.*
üìû For queries, contact *Dr. Vikas Raval* at +91 94293 56638

Don‚Äôt miss this opportunity to enhance your future ‚Äî *enroll now and say

Best wishes,

subject: anand-chaniyara-college, last-chance cert voucher, pick your Copilot model, join Hack Week & talk at Git Merge
snippet: GitHub Education Student Newsletter April 2025 Spring is full of growth‚Äîand we're not just talking about the trees. This month we're marking two decades of Git, prepping you for summer learning
content:
***********************************
GitHub Education Student Newsletter
***********************************

----------
April¬†2025
----------

Spring is full of growth‚Äîand we're not just talking about the trees. This month we‚Äôre marking two decades of Git, prepping you for summer learning, and sharing fresh opportunities to code for good.

*What's inside:*

* üéâ Git turns¬†20
* üß™ Certification voucher deadline
* ü§ñ Pick your perfect Copilot model
* üîì Global Hack Week: Open¬†Source
* üåç Earth-day saplings at IIT Bombay
* üå± Climate Action Plan for developers
* üßë‚Äçü¶Ø Emojis + plain-language tips
* üé§ Call for speakers: Git¬†Merge¬†2025

üéâ Git turns 20
--------------

‚ÄúI didn‚Äôt set out to change the world, I just needed a better tool.‚Äù In a 28-minute Q&A, Linus Torvalds looks back on *20¬†years of Git* ‚Äîfrom its lightning-fast nine-day creation to what‚Äôs next, from partial clones to virtual file systems. Come for the origin story, stay for Linus‚Äô advice to the next generation of maintainers.

Watch Linus' full Q&A ( https://github.blog/open-source/git/git-turns-20-a-qa-with-linus-torvalds/ )

üß™ June 30: cert vouchers expire
-------------------------------

Heads-up, Developer Pack members! The current batch of *free¬†GitHub Foundations exam vouchers* disappears on *June¬†30¬†2025*. Redeem yours now and schedule the test at your convenience. Vouchers will pause while we migrate to a new platform‚Äîbut they‚Äôll be back this fall and expanded to teachers, too. Need a refresher? Walk through the GitHub Foundations Learning Path ( https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/training/paths/github-foundations/ ) or tackle bite-size challenges at GitHub Skills ( https://skills.github.com/ ).

Don't miss out ( https://education.github.com/experiences/foundations_certificate )

ü§ñ Find your ideal Copilot model
-------------------------------

*Claude¬†3* ? *Gemini¬†1.5¬†Pro* ? *GPT-4o* ? Copilot now lets you switch among models from Anthropic, Google, and OpenAI. This guide breaks down latency, context length, and creative strengths, then offers a three-step framework to A/B test models in your own repos. Your takeaway: match the model to the job‚Äîcode completion, doc drafting, or architecture brainstorming‚Äîand swap any time from Settings¬†‚Üí¬†AI¬†models.

Explore the guide ( https://github.blog/ai-and-ml/github-copilot/a-guide-to-deciding-what-ai-model-to-use-in-github-copilot/ )

üîì Global Hack Week: Open¬†Source
-------------------------------

Seven days. Dozens of live workshops. Unlimited pull requests. From *May¬†9‚Äì15* , *MLH‚Äôs Global Hack Week* celebrates everything open source. Build alongside maintainers, tackle daily challenges for swag, and learn how to land your first contribution‚Äî100% free and fully virtual, so you can hack from wherever you are.

Claim your spot ( https://ghw.mlh.io/events/open-source )

üåç Earth-Day saplings at IIT Bombay
----------------------------------

Swag ‚Üí saplings. During COO Kyle Daigle‚Äôs campus visit, the IIT Bombay community swapped stickers for seedlings‚Äî *500 young trees* planted in partnership with SankalpTaru Foundation, inspired by Professor Varsha Apte. It‚Äôs a small but real step in our long-term sustainability roadmap: fewer material giveaways, more green giveaways.

See our climate work ( https://github.com/social-impact/focus-areas/environmental-sustainability )

üå± Climate Action Plan for developers
------------------------------------

Your pull requests can cut carbon. This *Climate Action Plan* surfaces tools like CodeCarbon (measure emissions) and Electricity Maps (track realtime grid intensity), plus a directory of 60K+ climate-tech repos. Whether you‚Äôre optimizing ML training or building low-energy front-ends, you‚Äôll find starter issues and best practices to green your workflow.

Dig into the plan ( https://github.com/social-impact/focus-areas/environmental-sustainability/climate-action-plan-for-developers )

üßë‚Äçü¶Ø A11y Skills: Emojis + plain language
----------------------------------------

*Week¬†3 of Accessibility Skills* dives into two quick wins: pick emojis with built-in meaning (‚úÖ over ‚Äú‚ú®‚Äù), and rewrite jargon-heavy docs into everyday language. The discussion thread includes worksheet examples, a linter you can drop into CI, and a challenge to update one paragraph of your README‚Äîthen share before-and-after screenshots.

Join the learning ( https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/157840 )

üé§ Call for speakers: Git Merge¬†2025
-----------------------------------

Got a Git story, workflow win, or research project worth sharing? *Git¬†Merge¬†2025* is now accepting talk proposals through *May¬†13*. Join a global lineup of developers, maintainers, and teams pushing Git forward‚Äîtravel assistance available for selected student speakers.

Submit your talk ( https://git-merge.com/ )

üëã Until next time
-----------------

That‚Äôs a wrap on April! Thanks for being part of the GitHub Education community. Keep building, keep learning, and we‚Äôll see you next month.

- The GitHub Education Team

Follow us

Instagram ( https://www.instagram.com/githubeducation/?hl=en ) Facebook ( https://www.facebook.com/GitHubEducation/ ) Threads ( https://www.threads.net/@githubeducation ) X / Twitter ( https://twitter.com/githubeducation ) Bluesky ( https://bsky.app/profile/githubeducation.bsky.social ) LinkedIn ( https://www.linkedin.com/showcase/github-education/ ) YouTube ( https://www.youtube.com/@githubeducation4427 ) Twitch ( https://www.twitch.tv/githubeducation )

subject: Arista Networks System Test Hiring Drive (April 2nd(onsite) and 4th(Remote)
snippet: Dear Candidates, We are excited to invite you to participate in our upcoming System Test Hiring Drive! Details: Onsite Interview: April 2nd, [Tower A, 11th floor, Global Tech Park, Marathahalli Outer
content:
Dear Candidates,

We are excited to invite you to participate in our upcoming *System Test
Hiring Drive*!

*Details:*

   - *Onsite Interview*: April 2nd, [Tower A, 11th floor, Global Tech Park,
   Marathahalli Outer Ring Road, Devarabeesanahalli Village, Varthur, Hobli,
   Bellandur, Bengaluru, Karnataka 560103]
   - *Remote Interview*: April 4th.

To confirm your participation and select your preferred date, please
register through the link below:

*Registration Link* <https://forms.gle/WRtTjGrS2pNNWRbt7>

*Important Notes:*

   - For the *onsite interview*, please be sure to arrive on time at the
   specified location.
   - The *remote interview* will be conducted via Google Meet. Please
   ensure your internet connection and devices are ready for a seamless
   experience.

Additionally, I have attached the *System Test Preparation Documents* and *Job
Description (JD)* links to help you prepare for the interview.

   - [System Test Preparation Documents Link]
   - [Job Description Link]

We look forward to seeing you at the event. If you have any questions or
need further information, feel free to reach out.

Thanks.

subject: The Quill: CHARUSAT Chronicles | Volume 10 - Issue 2
snippet: Welcome to Quill The Quill: CHARUSAT Chronicles Greetings from CHARUSAT! In the ever-evolving journey of academic excellence and innovation, we are delighted to introduce Quill ‚Äî the official
content:
[Welcome to Quill]
[https://mailer.charusat.org.in/index.php/campaigns/pj902x2k39ea7/track-url/ls409tohbwc79/cde86d8c0da7b957c934ecfd99c713dcf0d13606]


THE QUILL: CHARUSAT CHRONICLES

Greetings from CHARUSAT!

In the ever-evolving journey of academic excellence and innovation, we
are delighted to introduce QUILL ‚Äî the official newsletter of
CHARUSAT. True to its name, Quill embodies the spirit of creativity,
intellect, and expression that defines our vibrant community.

WHAT‚ÄôS INSIDE QUILL?

 	* ACCOLADES: CHARUSAT'S EXCELLENCE ‚Äì Celebrating extraordinary
accomplishments of our students, faculty, and alumni.
 	* RESEARCH PUBLICATIONS: THE EDGE OF EXPLORATION ‚Äì Showcasing
groundbreaking discoveries.
 	* EMINENT SPEAKERS: UNVEILING NEW PERCEPTIONS ‚Äì Dive into engaging
conversations and transformative ideas.
 	* CAMPUS BUZZ: CELEBRATING CAMPUS LIFE ‚Äì Experience the energy and
excitement of campus life.
 	* FACULTY SPOTLIGHT: ACADEMIC EXCELLENCE ‚Äì Highlighting the
brilliance of our faculty.
 	* STUDENT SPOTLIGHT: RISING STARS ‚Äì Inspiring stories of our
student community.

Quill is more than just a newsletter; it is a chronicle of our shared
vision, growth, and success. Join us in celebrating the milestones and
moments that make CHARUSAT a hub of inspiration and innovation.

[https://mailer.charusat.org.in/index.php/campaigns/pj902x2k39ea7/track-url/ls409tohbwc79/6a1d41c8c004b6b45507b44a8baa19329fc0135a]

Warm regards,
MR. KRUTEN PATEL
Executive Officer - Corporate Communications

subject: Fwd: Inauguration of IEEE CHARUSAT Student Branch - Women in Engineering (WIE)
snippet: ---------- Forwarded message --------- From: Principal CSPIT <principal.cspit@charusat.ac.in> Date: Fri, 7 Mar 2025, 9:36 am Subject: Inauguration of IEEE CHARUSAT Student Branch - Women in
content:
---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Principal CSPIT <principal.cspit@charusat.ac.in>
Date: Fri, 7 Mar 2025, 9:36‚ÄØam
Subject: Inauguration of IEEE CHARUSAT Student Branch - Women in
Engineering (WIE)
To: Charusat Family <charusatfamily@charusat.ac.in>



Inauguration of IEEE CHARUSAT Student Branch Women in Engineering Affinity
Group and Seminar talk on "Women Innovators in Tech: Success Stories and
Lessons Learned"

Newly Established IEEE CHARUSAT Student Branch Women in Engineering
Affinity Group invites all female students and faculties of CHARUSAT to
participate in the inauguration ceremony followed by a seminar talk.
About IEEE WIE

*Vision:* "To be globally recognized for its contributions in STEM fields.
Our goal is to facilitate the recruitment and retention of women in
technical disciplines globally. We envision a vibrant community of IEEE
women and men collectively using their diverse talents to innovate for the
benefit of humanity."

*Mission:* "To connect, support, and inspire women and girls worldwide, and
facilitate their recruitment and retention in STEM fields, fostering
technological innovation and excellence for the benefit of humanity."
Guest Speaker
Ruzan Khambatta

A visionary entrepreneur, social innovator, and passionate advocate for
women's empowerment. Through her groundbreaking initiatives like Wajra O'
Force, PoliceHEART 1091, and Halla Bol, she has transformed thousands of
lives. Her success mantra? Small steps today lead to giant leaps tomorrow!

Learn more about Ruzan Khambatta <https://ruzankhambatta.com/wizzo1/>
Event Details

   - *Date:* *10th March 2025*
   - *Time:* *9:45 AM to 11:00 AM*
   - *Venue:* *2nd floor, Seminar hall, CSPIT EC-EE(A6 building), CHARUSAT*

This event is a milestone moment as we officially launch the Student
Chapter of WiE Society of IEEE, a dedicated community to uplift and support
women in technology. Whether you're a student, professional, or tech
enthusiast, this is an opportunity to connect, learn, and be part of a
movement that drives change.

E-Certificates will be provided to all the participants.

Let's come together to celebrate, empower, and innovate!
Register Here
<https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1YtXFaNHx3A12jsPhcPr6jRjZWwjOh48EskA9I3Ra9Mg/edit>

Looking forward to your presence!

Regards,

https://stackblitz.emlnk1.com/lt.php?x=3DZy~GE5UIacD5B-ydDIWBGc1HAnutPvj-UvkKLDInCcEK.u_Ey.zuRs3I2ljdH2nutAYHbMKk 

Hey there,¬†

I'm back in your inbox with some exciting updates!

 Major Supabase upgrades landed
https://stackblitz.emlnk1.com/lt.php?x=3DZy~GE5UIacD5B-ydDIWBGc1HAnutPvj-UvkKLDInCcEK.u_Ey.zuRs3I2ljdH2nutAYHfFIk
We're thrilled to announce that the Bolt x Supabase integration just got even better!¬†¬†You can now connect your Bolt projects directly to your existing Supabase databases, pause and resume projects from Bolt, disconnect when needed, and configure details of a new project.¬†

Want to build both a web app and a mobile app? Great news - both can use the same Supabase database! This means less work for you and fewer headaches when managing your projects.¬†

Try it now! Click the Supabase button in the top right corner to explore all new connection options. Learn more in our announcement on X https://stackblitz.emlnk1.com/lt.php?x=3DZy~GE5UIacD5B-ydDIWBGc1HAnutPvj-UvkKLDInCcEK.u_Ey.zuRs3I2ljdH2nutAYHfFIk.

** More platform improvements¬†**

* 

**Smarter debugging:** We've implemented SotA debugging that uses advanced reasoning to solve problems faster (while using
90% fewer tokens). The first users get access today, with a full rollout happening over the next few weeks. Learn more in our announcement on X https://stackblitz.emlnk1.com/lt.php?x=3DZy~GE5UIacD5B-ydDIWBGc1HAnutPvj-UvkKLDInCcEK.u_Ey.zuRs3I2ljdH2nutAYHfFKk.

* 

**Fewer building errors:** We've implemented an update that means less of the "Failed building the project" error message.

* 

**Improved Expo experience:** We've enhanced the experience around handling images, icons, and fonts.

* 

**Faster performance:** We've upgraded our infrastructure so Bolt now boots and responds up to 5x faster, especially on slower connections.

As always, we'd love to hear your feedback! We have something big planned for next week so be sure to stay tuned!¬†

Happy building,¬†

**Eric Simons**

CEO & Co-Founder
Bolt.new / StackBlitz

content:
Belkasoft Learning Center ( https://belkasoft.thinkific.com/ )‚Äå

************
Hello Anand,
************

Welcome to Belkasoft Learning Center! Let‚Äôs get started.

Sign in URL: https://belkasoft.thinkific.com/users/sign_in

Email: d23ce186@charusat.edu.in

If you have signed in to participate in a particular course,
please, log in and check your Dashboard to see if you have been
enrolled.

If this is not the case, please wait up to 72H for our team to
check your profile and enroll you manually in the course.

If after 48 hours you are still not enrolled, please contact our
support team at support@belkasoft.com.

We hope you will enjoy the course and experience!

Your Belkasoft Learning Center team.

---------------
Explore Courses
---------------

Windows Forensics with Belkasoft 
( https://belkasoft.thinkific.com/courses/windows-forensics-with-belkasoft )
 - This course is designed for digital forensics investigators
who deal with Windows computers in their work. It offers an
opportunity to enhance your knowledge and gain hands-on
experience in discovering and analyzing Windows artifacts.

Android Forensics with Belkasoft 
( https://belkasoft.thinkific.com/courses/android-forensics-with-belkasoft )
 - This course is designed for digital forensics investigators
who need to deal with Android devices in their work and want to
enhance their knowledge and gain hands-on experience in Android
acquisition and analysis.

iOS Forensics with Belkasoft 
( https://belkasoft.thinkific.com/courses/ios-forensics-with-belkasoft )
 - This course is designed for digital forensics investigators
who need to deal with iOS devices in their work and want to
enhance their knowledge and gain hands-on experience in iOS
acquisition and analysis.

subject: CHARUSAT | FoH | Story Narrating Competition
snippet: Foundation Day 2025 Story Narrating Competition 2025 Jointly organized by Indukaka Ipcowala Institute of Management [IIIM] & Faculty of Humanities [FoH] "Unleash Your Imagination, Let Your
content:
[Foundation Day 2025]
[https://mailer.charusat.org.in/index.php/campaigns/ba137rl8rs736/track-url/ls409tohbwc79/20986db598676eb1ed549684c002d31f5728889c]


STORY NARRATING COMPETITION 2025

 Jointly organized by 

INDUKAKA IPCOWALA INSTITUTE OF MANAGEMENT [IIIM]
&
FACULTY OF HUMANITIES [FOH]

"Unleash Your Imagination, Let Your Story Shine!"

"Storytelling is an age-old art that captivates audiences, stimulates
imagination, and preserves cultural heritage. Join us in this exciting
event where stories come to life, imagination knows no bounds, and
voices create unforgettable experiences!" 

üåü ABOUT THE EVENT

STORY NARRATING COMPETITION 2025, organized under the theme
INDIAN KNOWLEDGE SYSTEM, is here to celebrate creativity, culture, and
storytelling!

üìÖ DATE & TIME: February 21, 2025 | 10:30 AM onwards 

üé≠ REGISTRATION DETAILS

 	* REGISTER BY: February 20, 2025
 	* STORY THEME: Folk Tales, Inspirational Stories, Mythological
Tales, or Fictional Narratives

Register Now
[https://mailer.charusat.org.in/index.php/campaigns/ba137rl8rs736/track-url/ls409tohbwc79/deffdbff2458022a5a6fc21a81761850f8a7161d]


üèÜ AWARDS & CERTIFICATIONS

 	* üèÖ WINNER & RUNNER-UP: Trophy
 	* üìú ALL PARTICIPANTS: Participation Certificate
 	* EVENT CONVENORS: Dr. Binit Patel | Dr. Bhaskar Pandya
 	* EVENT COORDINATOR: Dr. Kinjal Bhatia
 	* CONTACT INFORMATION: +91 9033395935
[https://mailer.charusat.org.in/index.php/campaigns/ba137rl8rs736/track-url/ls409tohbwc79/309b22b6c6cc4f64be972de0ba0d4daab6df6da8]

üì¢ GENERAL RULES

 	* The competition is open to all registered students. Participants
must confirm their registration before the event.
 	* The narration must be in English.
 	* Each participant will have a 3 to 5-minute time slot for their
narration. Exceeding the limit may result in a penalty.
 	* Minimal use of handheld props is allowed, but the focus should
remain on narration. Visual presentations are not permitted.
 	* The storytelling should be engaging, expressive, and creative.
Unique presentation styles are encouraged.
 	* Participants must narrate their stories from memory. Reading
directly from a script is not allowed.

üîπ JUDGING CRITERIA

 	* üìñ Content & Creativity
 	* üé§ Expression & Voice Modulation
 	* üíÉ Body Language & Presentation
 	* ‚è≥ Time Management
 	* üåü Overall Impact

üîπ ADDITIONAL GUILDELINES

 	* DRESS CODE: Participants should dress appropriately for their
narration. Costumes are optional but should not overpower the
storytelling.
 	* PUNCTUALITY: Participants must arrive at least 30 minutes before
their scheduled slot.

üé§ We can't wait to hear your stories! See you there! üé≠

-------------------------

With best Regards,
MR. KRUTEN PATEL
Executive Officer - Corporate Communications

subject: The Quill: CHARUSAT Chronicles | Volume 10 - Issue 1
snippet: Welcome to Quill The Quill: CHARUSAT Chronicles Greetings from CHARUSAT! In the ever-evolving journey of academic excellence and innovation, we are delighted to introduce Quill ‚Äî the official
content:
[Welcome to Quill]
[https://mailer.charusat.org.in/index.php/campaigns/wx675d1tcad9c/track-url/ls409tohbwc79/a31db465432dd089f9e892e8753dafb6c5467911]


THE QUILL: CHARUSAT CHRONICLES

Greetings from CHARUSAT!

In the ever-evolving journey of academic excellence and innovation, we
are delighted to introduce QUILL ‚Äî the official newsletter of
CHARUSAT. True to its name, Quill embodies the spirit of creativity,
intellect, and expression that defines our vibrant community.

WHAT‚ÄôS INSIDE QUILL?

 	* ACCOLADES: CHARUSAT'S EXCELLENCE ‚Äì Celebrating extraordinary
accomplishments of our students, faculty, and alumni.
 	* RESEARCH PUBLICATIONS: THE EDGE OF EXPLORATION ‚Äì Showcasing
groundbreaking discoveries.
 	* EMINENT SPEAKERS: UNVEILING NEW PERCEPTIONS ‚Äì Dive into engaging
conversations and transformative ideas.
 	* CAMPUS BUZZ: CELEBRATING CAMPUS LIFE ‚Äì Experience the energy and
excitement of campus life.
 	* FACULTY SPOTLIGHT: ACADEMIC EXCELLENCE ‚Äì Highlighting the
brilliance of our faculty.
 	* STUDENT SPOTLIGHT: RISING STARS ‚Äì Inspiring stories of our
student community.

Quill is more than just a newsletter; it is a chronicle of our shared
vision, growth, and success. Join us in celebrating the milestones and
moments that make CHARUSAT a hub of inspiration and innovation.

[Quill Cover Page]
[https://mailer.charusat.org.in/index.php/campaigns/wx675d1tcad9c/track-url/ls409tohbwc79/acc0b593868118ea4029db7c89d967632bd3964b]

Warm regards,
THE EDITORIAL TEAM
CHARUSAT

content:
[Convocation 2025]
[https://mailer.charusat.org.in/index.php/campaigns/ek299l8d7yebf/track-url/ls409tohbwc79/e45138cac2fcb313e48f69d8e518170e93b8d030]


DEAR ALL,

We are happy to inform you that the 14TH CONVOCATION CEREMONY OF
CHARUSAT will be live-streamed on YouTube. This year's convocation is
a special milestone as we celebrate 25 GLORIOUS YEARS OF ACADEMIC
EXCELLENCE.

Click here to Watch the Ceremony Live
[https://mailer.charusat.org.in/index.php/campaigns/ek299l8d7yebf/track-url/ls409tohbwc79/280d7aa3c6ab2dce0e4b5ea1d43afda06924cd1e]
DATE: January 4, 2025 | TIME: 5 pm onwards
We invite you to join us virtually and participate in this momentous
occasion. The ceremony will feature the conferment of degrees, awards,
and recognition of our students' outstandingvements.

Please feel free to share the link with your family and friends who
may be interested in watching the ceremony.

We look forward to your virtual presence!

subject: Canada Day by IDP ‚Äì A Unique Study Abroad Opportunity
snippet: Dear Students, We are delighted to inform you about an exciting opportunity to gain valuable insights into studying in Canada through the upcoming "Canada Day by IDP" event, exclusively
content:
Dear Students,



We are delighted to inform you about an exciting opportunity to gain
valuable insights into studying in Canada through the upcoming *"Canada Day
by IDP"* event, exclusively hosted for you at CHARUSAT University in
collaboration with IDP Education.



This event is designed to provide you with a comprehensive understanding of
the opportunities that await in Canada and address common misconceptions
about studying there. Highlights of the event include:



¬∑  *Expert Talk:* "Breaking the Myths about the Present Scenario of
Studying in Canada and Fact-Checking the Enormous Opportunities Awaiting in
Canada."



¬∑  *One-on-One Counseling:* Get personalized guidance and profile
assessments from IDP's Canada team experts.



¬∑  *On-the-Spot Solutions:* Address your queries directly with experienced
counselors.



*Event Details:*

¬∑  *Date:* Tuesday, December 31, 2024

¬∑  *Time:* 11:00 AM ‚Äì 4:00 PM

¬∑  *Venue:* IIIM Auditorium, CHARUSAT University Campus

¬∑  *Registration Link:* Register Here
<https://forms.gle/sNBS7gZavGohxxtG8> (Please
use your CHARUSAT email ID to register.)



This is a remarkable opportunity to explore the possibilities of studying
in Canada and receive tailored advice for the academic journey. We
encourage you to register and make the most of this exclusive event.



Seats are limited, so please register as soon as you can to secure your
participation.



If you have any questions, please get in touch with Dr. Vijay Makwana at
+91 99983 80041.




Thanks & Regards,

*Executive Officer (Corporate Communications)*

subject: Internships, certificates, challenges, and exclusive opportunities inside!
snippet: Kickstart your coding journey with Hack Club High Seas, internships, Advent of Code, and more! Student Newsletter November 2024 Hey anand-chaniyara-college, As November comes to a close, we have some
content:
Kickstart your coding journey with Hack Club High Seas, internships, Advent of Code, and more!

( https://github.com/education )

********************
*Student Newsletter*
********************

*************
November 2024
*************

Hey anand-chaniyara-college,
As November comes to a close, we have some great opportunities to share with you. In this newsletter, you'll find inspiring projects from fellow students, challenges to boost your skills, and resources to help you grow and connect with others. Whether you're ready to start something new, learn fresh skills, or join a community of developers, there's something here for you.

***********************************
Set sail with Hack Club High Seas üö¢
***********************************

( https://hack.club/high-seas-gh )

Join over *10,000 students* exploring the vast oceans of code with Hack Club High Seas ( https://hack.club/high-seas-gh ). With more than *2,000 projects* already shipped on GitHub, now's your chance to make waves and earn fantastic prizes while you learn and have fun!

Sail to High Seas ( https://hack.club/high-seas-gh )

There are *tons* of great prizes for you, including a Raspberry Pi 5, Flipper Zero, System76 Keeb, iPad, even a Framework laptop. And as if that wasn't enough, you also have the opportunity to win the special prize of a 1 on 1 call with:

*Guido van Rossum*

( https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guido_van_Rossum?mc_cid=5d4eb3c0c2&mc_eid=UNIQID )

Creator of the Python programming language.

*Anders Hejlsberg*

( https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anders_Hejlsberg?mc_cid=5d4eb3c0c2&mc_eid=UNIQID )

Lead architect of the C# programming language and the original author of Turbo Pascal and Delphi.

*Looking for inspiration to get started? Here are some cool new High Seas projects from the community:*

*Mathias* , a 14 year old from France, integrated DOOM in the GitHub contributions graph ( https://github.com/GH-DOOM/DOOM64 ) ü§Ø

*Lilia D* , a 16 year old from Florida, USA, created a personality quiz ( https://personalityquiz.kittycat.hackclub.app/ ) based on your dream pet üòπ

*Will K* , a 15 year old from Texas, USA, founded the nonprofit Crafts and Laughs ( https://craftsandlaughs.org/ ) to create handmade gifts for hospitalized children.

*Toshani,* a 16-year-old from Pennsylvania learning to code for the first time, shipped their first dynamic website: Boba customization shop ( https://codepen.io/CodingMasterGirl/pen/jOgogMM ) üßã

**********************************
GitHub Universe 2024 highlights üõ∞Ô∏è
**********************************

( https://github.blog/news-insights/product-news/universe-2024-previews-releases/ )

Catch up on the latest announcements ( https://github.blog/news-insights/product-news/universe-2024-previews-releases/ ) , product updates, and insights from the global developer community.

Read the blog ( https://github.blog/news-insights/product-news/universe-2024-previews-releases/ )

( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uh9A4LvuGHM&ab_channel=GitHub )

Watch @kdaigle‚Äôs Universe Day 2 keynote ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uh9A4LvuGHM&ab_channel=GitHub ) , featuring Hack Club High Seas‚Äô live launch on stage with student Acon.

Watch the VOD ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uh9A4LvuGHM&ab_channel=GitHub )

************************************
Get GitHub Foundations certified üßë‚Äçüéì
************************************

( https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/144443 )

Join a four-week guide to prepare for the *GitHub Copilot certification exam*. Actively participate to win exam vouchers.

Get started now ( https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/144443 )

( https://education.github.com/experiences/foundations_certificate )

Verified students with the Student Developer Pack can now take the *GitHub Foundations Certification* exam for free!

Get your certification ( https://education.github.com/experiences/foundations_certificate )

************************************************
Kickstart your career with GitHub Internships üá∫üá∏
************************************************

( https://www.github.careers/early-in-profession )

Summer 2025 GitHub Internship roles are open in the US and accepting applications from current university students. Engineering, Product, Operations and Revenue teams are recruiting summer interns. All roles are posted on our GitHub Career Page ( https://www.github.careers/early-in-profession ).

Check Intern roles ( https://www.github.careers/early-in-profession )

*****************************************
Level up with Microsoft MakeCode Arcade üëæ
*****************************************

( https://arcade.makecode.com/ )

Learn to code through play with Microsoft MakeCode Arcade ( https://arcade.makecode.com/ ). Create retro-style games using an intuitive block-based interface, and seamlessly transition to JavaScript or Python as you advance.

Start creating games ( https://arcade.makecode.com/ )

******************************************************
Export your Replit repls with the Hack Club Lifeboat üõü
******************************************************

( https://hackclub.com/replit/ )

Replit‚Äôs free plan may be gone, but Hack Club has you covered. Use their open-source tool to migrate your projects to GitHub ( https://hackclub.com/replit/ ) while keeping your file history as incremental commits. Plus, the first 5,000 users get free stickers!

Export your repls ( https://hackclub.com/replit/ )

******************************
GitHub Field Day highlights ‚òÇÔ∏è
******************************

üá≥üá¨ Abuja's GitHub Field Day brought 75 community leaders together to share knowledge, collaborate, and grow. The day was packed with interactive sessions, breakout discussions, and inspiring conversations, proving the power of connection in the developer community.

üáÆüá≥ Field Days in Delhi ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E59uxMjYtWA ) and Hyderabad ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=po-b1IUoyO4 ) carried the same spirit, bringing developers together to create, learn, and share. Watch the highlights:

( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=po-b1IUoyO4 )

( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E59uxMjYtWA )

**********************************
Countdown to Advent of code 2024 üìÜ
**********************************

( https://adventofcode.com/ )

Daily puzzles, endless possibilities! Advent of Code *kicks off on December 1* , offering fun challenges for developers at all skill levels. Join the global community and sharpen your problem-solving skills this holiday season.

Go to Advent of Code ( https://adventofcode.com/ )

*******************************************
Does GitHub Copilot improve code quality? ü§ñ
*******************************************

( https://github.blog/news-insights/research/does-github-copilot-improve-code-quality-heres-what-the-data-says/ )

Curious about how AI can impact your coding? Research shows that GitHub Copilot not only saves time but also helps write higher-quality code. Dive into the data and see how Copilot is transforming development.

Read the research ( https://github.blog/news-insights/research/does-github-copilot-improve-code-quality-heres-what-the-data-says/ )

****************************
Repo of the month: Docling üê•
****************************

( https://github.com/DS4SD/docling?tab=readme-ov-file )

Looking for a neat tool to simplify your projects? Check out Docling ( https://github.com/DS4SD/docling?tab=readme-ov-file ) , a community-driven repository that's making waves on GitHub! Docling effortlessly converts PDFs, DOCX, and more into Markdown or JSON, making it a handy resource for developers, like you.

Check out Docling ( https://github.com/DS4SD/docling?tab=readme-ov-file )

**************************************************
Appwrite Joins the GitHub Student Developer Pack üéâ
**************************************************

( https://appwrite.io/education )

Appwrite ( https://appwrite.io/education ) , an open-source Backend-as-a-Service platform for building web, mobile, and backend apps, is now part of the GitHub Student Developer Pack ( https://education.github.com/pack?sort=newest ). Verified students get free access to Appwrite Pro for the duration of their studies (a $15/month value).

Get started with Appwrite ( https://appwrite.io/education )

That‚Äôs it for this month! Do us a solid, will you? Share your projects and stories with us on GitHub Discussions ( https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/ ) - we‚Äôd love to see what you‚Äôre building.

snippet: Welcome to Global Campus! Your request to join has been approved. You can access Global Campus at https://education.github.com/globalcampus/student?email_referrer=true GitHub Education logo ‚ú® Welcome
content:
Hey Chaniyara Anand Jagdishbhai,

Welcome!

Thank you for joining https://education.github.com/globalcampus/student?email_referrer=true. GitHub Global Campus helps students, teachers, and schools access the tools and events they need to shape the next generation of software development.


  Congratulations, you are now a GitHub Global Campus student! You can now explore valuable offers provided by GitHub's partners in the GitHub Student Developer Pack, view student events, and much more when you sign in at:

    https://education.github.com/globalcampus/student?email_referrer=true

  If you are renewing your membership please be aware that some of our partner offers are single-use and non-renewable, and that you should contact the partner directly if you have any questions.


  Learn about GitHub Education's programs for students, like GitHub Campus Experts and our grants for first-time hackathons:
    https://education.github.com/students

  Introduce yourself to the GitHub Education Community:
    https://github.com/orgs/github-community/discussions/categories/github-education

  Your teacher or faculty advisor can request private repositories for your class projects or student club. Send them to:
    https://docs.github.com/en/github/teaching-and-learning-with-github-education

Give the gift of GitHub Education to your entire school:
  https://education.github.com/partners/schools

Have an Octotastic day!
- The GitHub Education Team

content:
Hey anand-chaniyara-college,

Unfortunately, we were unable to verify your academic affiliation based on the information you submitted on Sep 26, 2024 for @anand-chaniyara-college.

 - Please secure your GitHub account with two-factor authentication.  You may need to log out and log back in to GitHub before reapplying.
 - Please complete your GitHub billing information with your full name exactly as it appears in your academic affiliation document. You do not have to add a payment method. You may need to log out and log back in to GitHub before reapplying. If you have only a single legal name, enter it in both the first and last name fields.
 - Please use your device camera to submit academic affiliation documents. 
 - You are unlikely to be verified until you have completed your GitHub user profile with your full name exactly as it appears in your academic affiliation document. Please do not use a variation of your name or a nickname. Once you have updated your profile information log out and log back into GitHub before re-applying.
Once you have resolved the issues with your submission, visit https://education.github.com to reapply.

Have questions? Please seek help via our Student Developer Pack Application FAQ (https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/111352) or visit the GitHub Education Community (https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/categories/github-education).

<3 The GitHub Education Team

subject: NPTEL Newsletter: Reminder: Share Your Experience: Take the NPTEL Course Feedback Survey (10-15 min)
snippet: Dear Learner, We trust that you are doing well. We are reaching out to you with a request to take part in a survey, since you have registered/completed NPTEL course(s). The survey will take about 10 to
content:
Dear Learner,

We trust that you are doing well. We are reaching out to you with a request
to take part in a survey, since you have registered/completed NPTEL
course(s). The survey will take about 10 to 15 minutes of your time to
complete. The feedback provided will be used to refine and improve the
course pedagogy and processes. The survey has a mix of open ended and
closed ended questions. There are no right or wrong answers, but just your
viewpoints and they are of interest to us from a research standpoint.

All information collected would be kept STRICTLY confidential and used only
for internal research purposes. Neither the names nor the respondents‚Äô
identities will be revealed. Thank you for your valuable time.
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
*Deadline: May 31, 2024*
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

*Survey Link: https://forms.gle/rzpxj4Yf8tmqeFvB8
<https://forms.gle/rzpxj4Yf8tmqeFvB8>*

Those who have already filled the survey form may kindly ignore this email.

Thanks and Regards,
NPTEL TEAM.

--

subject: Important Notice:No CHANGE in NPTEL Exam Schedule for April 2024
snippet: Dear Student, We wanted to take a moment to address an important matter regarding the upcoming election dates and their potential impact on your exam schedule. None of the election dates clash with
content:
Dear Student,

We wanted to take a moment to address an important matter regarding the
upcoming election dates and their potential impact on your exam schedule.


   1.

   None of the election dates clash with scheduled exam dates. If we
   schedule additional dates, we will ensure they again do not clash with
   elections in your state.
   2.

   Hence this is to confirm that there will be no changes to the exam dates
   and they are the same as previously scheduled. We may have exams in some
   cities on April 19 and April 26 depending on seat availability on
   scheduled dates. But again this will be done ensuring we don't conduct
   exams on election dates in your state.
   3.

   Your academic progress and success remain our top priority, and we are
   committed to maintaining the integrity of the examination process.
   4.

   We have more than 6 lakh learners registered for April exams and
   logistics has been a huge challenge. We understand that some of you may
   need to travel to your native cities to participate in the voting process.
   Please remember that you selected your exam cities during registration, and
   it is crucial that you return to these cities to take your exams as
   scheduled. Since hall ticket and center allocation is under process, exam
   cities selected by you during exam registration cannot be changed now.


Hence, we kindly request that you make the necessary arrangements to ensure
you can both exercise your right to vote and fulfill your academic
obligations.

Warm Regards,

NPTEL Team.

Dear Students,



The prominent teacher from IIT Mandi, Dr. Aditya Nigam sir, is going to

helped so many enthusiastic to start career in the domain. You will also  
get the chance to interact with sir and to present your work. By attending  
this 5 days session, you get more knowledge in ML/DL which help you to  
build the career in ML/DL.
